    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi Neovim team!\n\nIn `0.11.0` and later, calling `nvim_win_set_hl_ns(winid, 0)` to reset a window to the global namespace has the side effect of permanently disabling `winhighlight` for that window.\n\nIn previous versions (`0.10.x`), setting the namespace to `0` would reset the window to the global namespace, but `winhighlight` would continue to work (or could be re-enabled). Now, once `0` is passed, the window ignores `winhighlight` settings entirely, even if `winhighlight` is unset and reset.\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun the following lua script:\n\n```\nlocal global_ns = 0\nlocal current_winid = 0\n\nvim.wo[current_winid].winhl = 'ColorColumn:Normal'\nprint('anonymous_ns_1=', vim.api.nvim_get_hl_ns({winid= current_winid}))\n\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_hl_ns(current_winid, global_ns)\nvim.wo[current_winid].winhl = ''\nvim.wo[current_winid].winhl = 'ColorColumn:Normal'\nprint('anonymous_ns_2=', vim.api.nvim_get_hl_ns({winid= current_winid}))\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n `anonymous_ns_1` and `anonymous_ns_2` should be some value > 0\n\n**Result (v0.11.0) and all later releases**:\n```\nanonymous_ns_1=2\nanonymous_ns_2=0\n```\n\n**Example (v0.10.4):**\n```\nanonymous_ns_1=2\nanonymous_ns_2=2\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2278+g88dc44260f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWin 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nPowershell\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\ndownload from github releases",
